label: Hitchhikers
description: Trustroots was started by hitchhikers for hitchhikers. Many people found out about Trustroots through Hitchwiki. Meet new friends while you are heading in the same direction. Whether you are a person asking for rides or a person giving them this is the circle for you.

label: Nomads
description: Whether you find yourself in a place for a day, week, month or year, this is the circle for the vagabonds and wanderers who find home wherever their head may lie.

label: Dumpster divers
description: Love turning trash into treasure? This circle is for you! A circle for those finding value hidden in our waste bins. Whether recycling, skipping, saving food, rescuing furniture, gleaning or something else entirely, find others like you in this dumpster loving circle. (Did you know about Trashwiki.org?)

label: Vegans & Vegetarians
description: For health, for the animals or for the earth. Join this tribe if you're vegan or vegetarian. (Still a bit small, Veganwiki.info is a project related to Trustroots.)

label: Hikers
description: For outdoorsy people who love hiking in nature. Would you like to find hosts who can recomend the best local hikes? Maybe they will join you on the hike. This circle is for those who love to be active on their feet outdoors.

label: Ecoliving
description: Are you interested in living with less impact on our planet? Maybe you are already doing so and want to share and connect. For those who desire a life with less footprint, this circle welcomes you.

label: Foodsharing
attribution: Foodsharing.de & Offenblen.de: Foodsharing.de is a German website to rescue food in cooperation with stores. This circle was intended for Foodsharing activists and members, but by now, if you love sharing food with random strangers, join this, invite travellers to your home for lunch or dinner.
description: Foodsharing.de activists and members.

label: Cyclists
description: Legs of steel or maybe just some grand tour ambitions?  Cyclists connect with this circle, before, during and after you hit the road.

label: Musicians
description: Love jamming with other musicians? This circle can be good way to find them.

label: Artists
description: Creators & Creatives: love to talk about your latest project? Want a host or guest who can connect with you creatively? This is the circle for you.

label: Spirituals
description: Ever spend time wondering if there is something more to life? This circle is for you no matter what you believe.

label: Yoga
description: For practitioners of yoga: meet your fellows in this circle for yogis and yoginis.

label: Dancers
description: Dancing for fun, dancing as a release, dancing as a connection with others... whatever gets your booty shaking is fine with us. Join this circle and get into the groove. Modern dance, salsa, African dance... what ever might be your thing! Anyone who's into any sort of artisitic human movement!

label: Climbers
description: Climbers & mountain lovers: come meet fellow climbers and share your favorite spots to climb in this circle for climbers.

label: Rainbow gathering
description: Join this circle if you feel part of the Rainbow Family. It's great to camp in nature with hippies. Food circle, now!

label: Punks
description: This circle is so punk, we don´t even have a definition. Are you punk? Join us!

label: LGBTQ
description: A circle for lesbian, gay, bi, trans, queer people and their allies.

label: Hackers
description: Not afraid of :(){ :|:& };: - join fellow hackers this circle for ubergeeks. As a bonus, come help us build this site!.

label: Cooking
description: From bon vivant to utter gluttony, as long as you make it yourself or together it’s all good!

label: Van life
description: For folks hitting the nomadic road in their vans, camper vans, motorhomes, buses or what have you! If your van is big enough, consider hosting folks for a night.

label: Photographers
description: Worth more than a thousand words in a Circle description.

label: Buskers
description: Whether its music, art, theatre or any other kind of performance, find other buskers and street performers in this circle.

label: Families
description: It's great to share hospitality with kids. If you're a small or bigger family, please join this circle. It's nice to host travelling families — and as a travelling family it's great to meet other families while travelling.

label: Gardeners & Farmers
description: Regardless of whether you have a small urban balcony garden or enough land to live completely off-grid, this is the place for you!

label: Trustroots Volunteers
description: Join this circle if you want to help grow Trustroots — or if you are already helping. This makes it easier to work on Trustroots together, e.g. to organize an adhoc mini-collective. See also our volunteering page.

label: Sailors
description: For sailors and seafarers. Landlubbers beware! These waters are for sailors and seafarers...

label: Naturists
description: Feel better in your birthday suit? A circle for those practising, advocating and defending personal and social nudity — either individually, in the family or out and about.

label: Feminists
description: A feminst is anyone who recognizes the equality and full humanity of women and men.

label: Anarchists
description: In an anarchist society people wouldn't feel as though there was power because everyone would have equal footing.

label: Acroyoga
description: Practitioners of acroyoga: like your yoga with a partner or two? Or maybe even upside down? Connect with acroyoga people by joining this circle.

label: Squatters
description: The land belongs to those who work it, and a house to those who live in it. N’est-ce pas?

label: Surfers
description: Vitamin SEA is all we need. Do you feel at home in the water with a board: this is the place for you. Wave-, kite-, wind- and body-surfers find your fellow thalassophiles here. See you in the water.

label: Jugglers
description:
Juggling community: bring your juggling balls, bowling pins, swords and torches! If you are a juggler or have an interest in juggling this is the community for you.
Jugglers page on the Trustroots Wiki.

label: Slackliners
description: Joining this circle is as easy as falling off a 4cm piece of rope...

label: Lindyhoppers
description: The Lindy hop swing dance community. Hey daddy-o! Dance on over and join your fellow lovers of Lindy Hop and Swing!

label: Burners
description: Burning man community.

label: Circus
description: Are you rolling through life on one wheel regularly? Do you love swinging on a trapeze? Is walking on a thin rope as normal to you as walking on flat surfaces? Does performing any of the arts of the circus makes you incredibly happy? See where your fellow enthusiasts are by joining this circle.

label: Skateboarders
description: The streets are your playground. Whether you prefer a skateboard, a longboard or cruiser, join this rolling community to find your fellow wheel enthusiasts.

label: Beer brewers
description: No need to be a monk these days, just an enthusiast for this craft. Find you fellow brewers here to exchange recipes, get advice and of course enjoy a homemade crafted beer together. Bottoms up!

label: Winemakers
description: The soil, the sun, the grape, the casting, it all influences the taste when creating wine. If wine is more to you then “a good wine” then this is the place to find you equals.

label: Ravers
description: Love dancing your ass off to beats in underground and secret locations? Come join and find out where the party is at around the world. If you know, you know.

label: Zero-wasters
description: Interested in reducing the waste going to landfill and incineration ? Connect here with people acting individually and collectively towards a waste free world.

label: Scuba divers
description: If you love spending more time underwater than above land exploring amazing worlds, then this circle may be good for you.

label: Filmmakers
description: Aaaand action! Holding a camera, being in front of it, working on the tech side of things, traveling to find the best settings: if this all seems familiar to you, this is the circle to join. Find fellow enthusiasts, exchange experiences, work together on projects and of course travel the world.

label: Activists
description: Power to the people! No oceans, no life! Make love not war! Join this circle to find your fellow activists, add your protests on the map and join eachother in making the world a better place.

label: Runners
description: Anywhere you travel, your running shoes come with? The more miles the better? You even travel for big competitions? Weither you're a casual-, free-, marathon- or trail runner, this is the group for you.
